## Step-by-Step Setup

### 1. SMS Channel Options

| Platform | Cost | Features | Best For |
|----------|------|----------|----------|
| **Remind** | Free (edu) | 2-way texting, polls, broadcasts | Easiest setup |
| **Google Voice** | Free | Personal number, forwarding | Smallest pilot |
| **Textedly** | $30/mo | Keyword triggers, automation | Scaling later |

**Recommendation:** Start with Remind (free, educator-focused) OR Google Voice (zero setup).

### 2. Questionnaire Delivery

**Option A: Link-Based (Recommended)**
```
RA texts: "Hey [Name]! Quick 2-min check-in: [Google Form link]"
Student: Clicks link â†’ answers in mobile browser â†’ submits
Data: Lands in Google Sheet automatically
```

**Option B: Pure SMS (Keyword Replies)**
```
RA texts: "Ready for check-in? Reply START"
Student: "START"
System: "Q1: Rate your week 1-5"
Student: "3"
System: "Q2: Feeling down? 1=Not at all, 2=Several days..."
...
```

### 3. Google Forms Setup

Create form with sections matching questionnaire:

```
SECTION A: HOW'S IT GOING?
â”œâ”€â”€ Q1: Week rating (Linear scale 1-5)
â”œâ”€â”€ Q2-Q5: PHQ-4 items (Multiple choice: Not at all â†’ Nearly every day)
â”œâ”€â”€ Q6: Sleep quality (Linear scale 1-5)
â””â”€â”€ Q7: Life satisfaction (Linear scale 0-10)

SECTION B: CONNECTIONS
â”œâ”€â”€ Q8-Q10: UCLA-3 (Multiple choice: Hardly ever â†’ Often)
â””â”€â”€ Q11-Q13: Belonging (Linear scale 1-5)

SECTION C: STRESSORS
â”œâ”€â”€ Q14: Energy drains (Checkboxes)
â””â”€â”€ Q15: Resources wanted (Checkboxes)

SECTION D: FOLLOW-UP
â”œâ”€â”€ Q16: Want to meet? (Multiple choice)
â””â”€â”€ Q17: Anything else? (Paragraph - optional)
```

### 4. Google Sheets Scoring Dashboard

**Tab 1: Raw Responses** (auto-populated from Form)

**Tab 2: Scored Data** (add formulas)
```
| Name | PHQ2 | GAD2 | UCLA3 | Belong | Index | Flags |
|------|------|------|-------|--------|-------|-------|
| =A2  | =SUM(C2:D2) | =SUM(E2:F2) | =SUM(H2:J2) | =AVG(K2:M2) | [formula] | =IF(PHQ2>=3,"âš ï¸","") |
```

**Scoring Formulas:**
```
PHQ-2:     =SUM(Q2_response + Q3_response)      // 0-6
GAD-2:     =SUM(Q4_response + Q5_response)      // 0-6
UCLA-3:    =SUM(Q8 + Q9 + Q10)                  // 3-9
Belonging: =AVERAGE(Q11, Q12, Q13)             // 1-5

Wellbeing Index (simplified):
=ROUND(100 - (PHQ2/6*25 + GAD2/6*20 + (UCLA3-3)/6*20 + (5-Belong)/4*15 + (5-Sleep)/4*10 + (10-LifeSat)/10*10))

Flags:
=IF(PHQ2>=3, "ðŸŸ¡ Depression", "") & IF(UCLA3>=7, "ðŸŸ¡ Loneliness", "") & IF(PHQ2>=5, "ðŸ”´ URGENT", "")
```

**Tab 3: RD Dashboard** (aggregates)
```
| Floor | Avg Index | % Green | % Yellow | % Orange/Red | Top Stressor |
|-------|-----------|---------|----------|--------------|--------------|
| 3E    | =AVERAGEIF(...) | =COUNTIF(...)/COUNT(...) | ... | ... | =MODE(...) |
```

### 5. Alert Protocol (Manual but Effective)

```
DAILY WORKFLOW:

Morning:
â”œâ”€â”€ Check Sheet for new submissions
â”œâ”€â”€ Sort by "Flags" column
â””â”€â”€ Review any ðŸ”´ RED immediately

Per Submission:
â”œâ”€â”€ ðŸŸ¢ GREEN (no flags): Log as complete
â”œâ”€â”€ ðŸŸ¡ YELLOW (1 flag): Schedule RA follow-up within 1 week
â”œâ”€â”€ ðŸŸ  ORANGE (2+ flags): RA follow-up within 48 hrs, notify RD
â””â”€â”€ ðŸ”´ RED (urgent): Immediate door knock, RD involved

Weekly:
â”œâ”€â”€ Review aggregate trends
â”œâ”€â”€ Identify floor-wide patterns
â””â”€â”€ Plan targeted interventions
```

### 6. Email Alerts Setup

Use Google Apps Script (no coding knowledge needed):

```javascript
// Paste in Tools > Script Editor > Save > Set trigger
function checkForAlerts() {
  var sheet = SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSpreadsheet().getSheetByName('Scored Data');
  var data = sheet.getDataRange().getValues();

  for (var i = 1; i < data.length; i++) {
    var flags = data[i][6];  // Adjust column index for Flags
    if (flags.includes('ðŸ”´')) {
      MailApp.sendEmail(
        'rd@school.edu',
        'ðŸ”´ URGENT CheckIn Alert',
        'Resident ' + data[i][0] + ' flagged urgent. Review immediately.'
      );
    }
  }
}
```

Set trigger: Run `checkForAlerts` on form submission.

## Pilot Timeline

```
WEEK 1: SETUP
â”œâ”€â”€ Create Google Form (1 hour)
â”œâ”€â”€ Build scoring Sheet (2 hours)
â”œâ”€â”€ Test with 3 mock submissions
â””â”€â”€ Train RAs on protocol (30 min meeting)

WEEKS 2-3: SOFT LAUNCH
â”œâ”€â”€ 10-15 residents per RA
â”œâ”€â”€ Daily monitoring by RD
â”œâ”€â”€ Fix any issues
â””â”€â”€ Gather RA feedback

WEEKS 4-10: FULL PILOT
â”œâ”€â”€ All RA residents (~150-200 total)
â”œâ”€â”€ Weekly check-ins (or bi-weekly)
â”œâ”€â”€ Track: completion rate, flag accuracy, interventions
â””â”€â”€ Document case studies (anonymized)

WEEKS 11-12: ANALYSIS & PRESENTATION
â”œâ”€â”€ Export all data
â”œâ”€â”€ Calculate: % screened positive, avg wellbeing, trend
â”œâ”€â”€ Compare: flagged residents vs. unflagged outcomes
â””â”€â”€ Build presentation for institution
```

## Presentation Metrics to Collect

| Metric | Why It Matters |
|--------|----------------|
| Completion rate | "87% of residents completed check-ins" |
| Depression screening | "14% screened positive for depression symptoms" |
| Early interventions | "23 residents connected to counseling before crisis" |
| Trend detection | "Identified 8 residents with declining trajectories" |
| Floor patterns | "Floor 3E had elevated loneliness; implemented study groups" |
| Time savings | "RAs identified at-risk residents in 2 min vs. 30 min meetings" |

## Cost Summary

| Item | Cost | Notes |
|------|------|-------|
| Google Forms/Sheets | $0 | Use institutional Google Workspace |
| Remind (optional) | $0 | Free for educators |
| Your time | ~5 hrs/week | Decreases after setup |
| **Total** | **$0** | Scale justifies investment later |

